Distributed Spark Cluster Setup
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line knowledge
Understanding of distributed computing concepts
Familiarity with Java/Scala basics
SSH and networking fundamentals
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Install and configure Apache Spark in distributed mode
Set up a master-worker cluster architecture on a single machine
Configure Spark cluster communication
Submit and monitor distributed Spark jobs
Verify cluster functionality through test applications
Environment Setup
System Requirements
Linux machine (Ubuntu 20.04+ or CentOS 7+)
Minimum 4GB RAM
Java 8 or 11 installed
Root or sudo access
Initial Setup
Verify Java Installation
java -version
If Java is not installed:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk -y
Set Environment Variables
echo 'export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-11-openjdk-amd64' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
Task 1: Install and Configure Apache Spark
Step 1: Download Spark
cd ~
wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/spark/spark-3.4.1/spark-3.4.1-bin-hadoop3.tgz
tar -xzf spark-3.4.1-bin-hadoop3.tgz
sudo mv spark-3.4.1-bin-hadoop3 /opt/spark
Step 2: Configure Environment Variables
cat >> ~/.bashrc << 'EOF'
export SPARK_HOME=/opt/spark
export PATH=$PATH:$SPARK_HOME/bin:$SPARK_HOME/sbin
export PYSPARK_PYTHON=python3
EOF

source ~/.bashrc
Step 3: Configure Spark Properties
Create the Spark configuration file:

cd $SPARK_HOME/conf
cp spark-env.sh.template spark-env.sh
Edit spark-env.sh and add:

cat >> spark-env.sh << 'EOF'
export SPARK_MASTER_HOST=localhost
export SPARK_MASTER_PORT=7077
export SPARK_WORKER_CORES=2
export SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=2g
export SPARK_WORKER_INSTANCES=2
EOF
Step 4: Configure Spark Defaults
cp spark-defaults.conf.template spark-defaults.conf
Add these configurations to spark-defaults.conf:

spark.master                     spark://localhost:7077
spark.executor.memory            1g
spark.driver.memory              1g
spark.executor.cores             1
Task 2: Start and Configure the Spark Cluster
Step 1: Start the Spark Master
$SPARK_HOME/sbin/start-master.sh
Verify the master is running:

jps | grep Master
Access the Master Web UI at: http://localhost:8080

Step 2: Start Spark Workers
Start two worker instances:

$SPARK_HOME/sbin/start-worker.sh spark://localhost:7077
sleep 5
$SPARK_HOME/sbin/start-worker.sh spark://localhost:7077
Verify workers are running:

jps | grep Worker
Check the Web UI to confirm both workers are registered.

